NAME parkour_basic
DESC Basic parkour movement validation — double jump, wall run, slide
MAP parkour1

# Start in first person
VIEW first
WAIT 3
NOTE Player spawned in parkour1 map

# Walk forward to get a feel for the spawn area
CONSOLE +forward
WAIT 2
CONSOLE -forward
NOTE Walked forward in spawn area

# Test double jump: jump and then jump again in air
CONSOLE +moveup
WAIT 0.3
CONSOLE -moveup
WAIT 0.2
CONSOLE +moveup
WAIT 0.3
CONSOLE -moveup
WAIT 2
NOTE Double jump attempted — should have gotten extra height

# Switch to third person to see movement
VIEW third
WAIT 1

# Move forward and try running along the left wall
CONSOLE +forward
CONSOLE +moveleft
WAIT 0.5
CONSOLE -moveleft
WAIT 1

# Try a jump near a wall for wall run
CONSOLE +moveup
WAIT 0.3
CONSOLE -moveup
WAIT 2
CONSOLE -forward
NOTE Wall run attempt near wall — checking if player attaches

# Test crouch slide: run fast then crouch
CONSOLE +forward
WAIT 2
CONSOLE +movedown
WAIT 1
CONSOLE -movedown
CONSOLE -forward
WAIT 1
NOTE Crouch slide attempted — should maintain speed while ducked

# First person view for final check
VIEW first
WAIT 2
NOTE Parkour basic test complete
